comments.body:
This error occurs when a submitter who is not an admin views an unfinished submission's show page and tries to download the file.

The submitter of the object itself can still download the file, and moderators/admins can download the file.  I was able to replicate this error locally by submitting a file as one non-admin user, then logging in as another non-admin user and trying to download from the show page like the one in the screenshot above.

Small PR for the missing translation incoming.

princeton_ansible.title: Add responsible rate limiting to the catalog

comments.body: As part of this, @sandbergja created a chart of "rate limiting by IP" on our Datadog [nginx dashboard](https://app.datadoghq.com/dashboard/5p4-ifi-u45/nginx-pul-overview?from_ts=1689773809294&to_ts=1689946609294&live=false). And @maxkadel suggested creating a custom error page for users who are rate-limited. We could possibly do this by specifying a custom HTTP status code (under Error Code Sent to Client [here](https://www.nginx.com/blog/rate-limiting-nginx/)) and then creating a custom error page for that code that would include links to our open dataset and also contact info for the dev team for folks who think their legitimate requests are being rate-limited.
